100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 28, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, as member nations sought to address escalating tensions in Europe following the aftermath of World War I. In the United States, the ongoing debate over Prohibition intensified, with increasing reports of illegal speakeasies and bootlegging operations. Meanwhile, in the realm of science, notable advancements were made in the study of radioactivity, marking significant progress in the field of nuclear physics.
